cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of the topology of cellular networks. The use of algebraic geometric tools and metrics such as Betti numbers and Euler characteristics also suggests a possible fit with the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. The study of the effectiveness of large-scale deployment of base stations may also relate to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of log-normal distribution in the analysis may suggest a possible fit with the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-category.
